notes.note: Customer called, says he has had issues with her vehicle ever since the day she bought it. Says while driving home from the dealer, noticed a shaking/vibration present with and without brake pedal application when driving around 40 km/h. Also noticed a clunking noise that was worse with brake pedal application. Took vehicle back, told her to keep driving it, it was just the new brakes being broken in. Customer continued to drive it but continued to have issues, so she took it back again. They replaced brakes on the car and let her go. Noticed there was still a hesitation when trying to accelerate. Was out and about over the weekend, tried to start car but car would not start. Bought a battery and replaced it thinking this was the cause, did not correct. Towed to shop where she bought car and asked to have it diagnosed. Could not duplicate concern. Informed customer to wait until the issue occurs again and try to have them verify it and hopefully rectify it. Informed she cannot put in any claims related to this concern as it is a pre-existing condition. Will escalated if selling dealer absolutely refuses to assist. M.P.

notes.note: Rep from D & J Motors emailed back, says while they were removing the cylinder head, had a lot of difficulty removing some of the cylinder head bolts. Seized. Damaged block trying to remove them. Looked it up and found that this is a common concern and also found that Kia currently has a tsb for this concern. Called kia and vehicle falls within the tsb km and time stipulation, customer is able to bring vehicle there and have kia replace the whole engine for her to correct the concern. Shop mentioned they had 6 hours worth of work into the vehicle up until the point where they were no longer able to work on it. Need to settle up on 6 hours worth of repair. Called and spoke to Adam, Adam agreed to contribute 3 hours of labour to this shop even though the work that has been performed so far can be considered diagnostic. Sent shop revised break down of authorized labour (3.0 hours x $125/h), and informed them that the customer is responsible for the remaining balance of the repair work. M.P.
